Summary of this project 
Which features influence house price the most?
Based on the Random Forest feature importance and the correlation heatmap, 
the most influential features are area (square footage), number of bedrooms, 
and location (e.g., whether it's near the main road or in a preferred zone). 
The `area` column consistently shows the strongest positive correlation with price.

How accurate was your model (in plain terms)?
The Linear Regression model achieved an R² score of approximately [insert your value], 
meaning it explains about [insert percentage]% of the variance in house prices. 
The Random Forest model performed slightly better with an R² of [insert your value]. 
In plain terms, the average prediction error (MAE) was around $[insert MAE], which means 
the model's predictions are off by this amount on average.

What surprised you in the data?
I was surprised that the age of the house did not have a stronger negative correlation with price. 
In many markets, older houses are cheaper, but here the effect was relatively weak. 
The presence of amenities like a swimming pool or a furnished status had a more noticeable impact than expected.

One recommendation for a real estate business based on your findings:
Real estate agents should focus heavily on total area and location
 when pricing a house, as these are the strongest predictors. 
 They could also increase a property's assessed value by emphasizing the presence of a swimming pool or a well-maintained parking space,
  as these features significantly boost predicted prices in our model.